.TH "TEMPORAL.ZONEDDATETIME.INLEAPYEAR" "3JS" "December 8, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
Temporal.ZonedDateTime.inLeapYear \-
Temporal.ZonedDateTime.prototype.inLeapYear
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]inLeapYear\f[B]\f[R] accessor property of
\f[CR]Temporal.ZonedDateTime\f[R] instances returns a boolean indicating
whether this date is in a leap year.
A leap year is a year that has more days (due to a leap day or leap
month) than a common year.
It is calendar\-dependent.
.PP
The set accessor of \f[CR]inLeapYear\f[R] is \f[CR]undefined\f[R].
You cannot change this property directly.
.PP
For general information and more examples, see
\f[CR]Temporal.PlainDate.prototype.inLeapYear\f[R].
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Using inLeapYear
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] dt = Temporal.ZonedDateTime.from(\(dq2021\-07\-01[America/New_York]\(dq);
console.log(dt.inLeapYear); \f[I]// false\f[R]
console.log(dt.daysInYear); \f[I]// 365\f[R]
console.log(dt.monthsInYear); \f[I]// 12\f[R]
.EE
